page.title: 04More Ecology-the Butley Area
page.content: The area contains the Thicks, which is a primeval forest. In The Thicks there were some signs of life,mostly Rabbits and Deer.We found woodlice in dead wood and spiders webs it was very interesting.There is a game keeper to keep down the numbers of vermin,and he keeps people out.The Forestry Commission land we did not see much wild life but mostly deer live round there.Near Butley creek there was a lot of bird life such as wood pigeons,Pheasents,Sparrows and blackbirds.Rabbits and Hares are mostly seen round there.Flies are attracted to the swamp lands and also small water insects.There is a crag pit which is a home for burrowing animals.In the water meadow we saw coypu traps.we saw some birds such as lapwings and duck.There were insects like dragonflies and gnats.
